commit.message: Mark recent support tickets as backported

And is latest that still supports Python 3.4

Experiment with quick sdist-and-test checks in Travis

Can't wait to move to Circle so I can do this testing locally
fixed malformed PEM files -- there should not be leading spaces
Bump travis Py3.8 cell to non dev, and die on fail
Newer flake8 for Python 3.8 CI compat, and related tweaks

fix RSA key loading: p and q were being swapped

This currently works, because OpenSSL simply re-computes iqmp when it doesn't match the p & q values. However a future pyca/cryptography patch enforces this.
